{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MLWr2C5k9qgr9iKttGbTXR","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 2)\n     2→\n     3→### 10-2-nodejs-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T07:58Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Observation:** Existing `10-2-nodejs-provider.md` had minimal 3-AC version; overwrote with detailed 18-AC version with task breakdown and verification tags.\n     6→- **Observation:** `CoverageToolInfo` type mismatch between `stacks/types.ts` (`{ tool, configFile? }`) and `coverage.ts` (`{ tool, runCommand, reportFormat }`). Story notes this — reconciliation deferred to story 10-5.\n     7→- **Risk:** Epic AC3 says \"remove all Node.js if/else branches from consumers\" but incremental migration strategy defers this to 10-5. Replaced with AC18 (zero regressions) to match actual intent.\n     8→- **Problems:** None.\n     9→- **Workarounds:** None.\n    10→\n    11→### 10-2-nodejs-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:02Z)\n    12→\n    13→- **OtlpResult type mismatch:** `stacks/types.ts` (`{ success, packagesInstalled, error? }`) differs from `otlp.ts` (`{ status, packages_installed, start_script_patched, env_vars_configured, error? }`). Provider uses stacks/types version. Reconciliation deferred to 10-5.\n    14→- **`patchStartScript` optional on interface but implemented.** Consumers need optional chaining `provider.patchStartScript?.(dir)`.\n    15→- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~50 type errors in other test files (bridge, run, deps, etc.) unrelated to this story.\n    16→- **Consumer branches not removed** (by design per spec). Story 10-5 handles migration.\n    17→- **Test results:** 64/64 nodejs tests pass. Full suite: 3253 tests, 0 regressions.\n    18→\n    19→### 10-2-nodejs-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T08:07Z)\n    20→\n    21→- **HIGH (fixed):** `parseTestOutput()` vitest regex didn't capture skipped count — total was wrong.\n    22→- **HIGH (fixed):** `parseTestOutput()` jest regex failed when `skipped` appeared between `passed` and `total`. Rewrote to extract fields independently.\n    23→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `utils.ts` at 70.58% coverage (below 80% floor) — `readTextSafe()` untested. Added utils.test.ts with 9 tests.\n    24→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `nodejs.ts` catch branch in `patchStartScript` for malformed JSON untested. Added test.\n    25→- **LOW (not fixed):** `readTextSafe` catch branch (93.33%) — race condition between existsSync/readFileSync, not worth mocking.\n    26→- **LOW (not fixed):** `registry.ts` at 94.73% — lines from story 10-1, not in scope.\n    27→- **Coverage:** 97.09% overall, all 128 files above 80% floor. 3267 tests, 0 regressions.\n    28→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e39a20db-e648-4f8f-85ec-e4fa22cf8d05","uuid":"7be18c64-28e0-4d49-b77e-964a0a60e4cc","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:24.814Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 2)\n\n### 10-2-nodejs-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T07:58Z)\n\n- **Observation:** Existing `10-2-nodejs-provider.md` had minimal 3-AC version; overwrote with detailed 18-AC version with task breakdown and verification tags.\n- **Observation:** `CoverageToolInfo` type mismatch between `stacks/types.ts` (`{ tool, configFile? }`) and `coverage.ts` (`{ tool, runCommand, reportFormat }`). Story notes this — reconciliation deferred to story 10-5.\n- **Risk:** Epic AC3 says \"remove all Node.js if/else branches from consumers\" but incremental migration strategy defers this to 10-5. Replaced with AC18 (zero regressions) to match actual intent.\n- **Problems:** None.\n- **Workarounds:** None.\n\n### 10-2-nodejs-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:02Z)\n\n- **OtlpResult type mismatch:** `stacks/types.ts` (`{ success, packagesInstalled, error? }`) differs from `otlp.ts` (`{ status, packages_installed, start_script_patched, env_vars_configured, error? }`). Provider uses stacks/types version. Reconciliation deferred to 10-5.\n- **`patchStartScript` optional on interface but implemented.** Consumers need optional chaining `provider.patchStartScript?.(dir)`.\n- **Pre-existing TS errors:** ~50 type errors in other test files (bridge, run, deps, etc.) unrelated to this story.\n- **Consumer branches not removed** (by design per spec). Story 10-5 handles migration.\n- **Test results:** 64/64 nodejs tests pass. Full suite: 3253 tests, 0 regressions.\n\n### 10-2-nodejs-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T08:07Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `parseTestOutput()` vitest regex didn't capture skipped count — total was wrong.\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `parseTestOutput()` jest regex failed when `skipped` appeared between `passed` and `total`. Rewrote to extract fields independently.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `utils.ts` at 70.58% coverage (below 80% floor) — `readTextSafe()` untested. Added utils.test.ts with 9 tests.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `nodejs.ts` catch branch in `patchStartScript` for malformed JSON untested. Added test.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `readTextSafe` catch branch (93.33%) — race condition between existsSync/readFileSync, not worth mocking.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `registry.ts` at 94.73% — lines from story 10-1, not in scope.\n- **Coverage:** 97.09% overall, all 128 files above 80% floor. 3267 tests, 0 regressions.\n","numLines":28,"startLine":1,"totalLines":28}}}
