{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0198hcPXYz8mSTKYCzu6GNqt","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-3: Implement PythonProvider\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want all Python-specific logic in one file,\n     9→So that Python behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` exists, when inspected, then it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Python: requirements.txt/pyproject.toml/setup.py detection, coverage.py, pip/pipx OTLP packages, Dockerfile template <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given all Python if/else branches are removed from consumer files, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→\n    16→## Technical Notes\n    17→\n    18→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern).** Same structure as NodejsProvider.\n    19→\n    20→Extract Python-specific logic from these current locations:\n    21→\n    22→- **Coverage detection**: `src/lib/coverage.ts` has Python coverage.py detection. Move into `PythonProvider.detectCoverageConfig()`.\n    23→- **Test output parsing**: `src/lib/coverage.ts` `parseTestCounts()` has pytest output patterns (`X passed, Y failed`). Move into `PythonProvider.parseTestOutput()`.\n    24→- **Coverage report parsing**: `src/lib/coverage.ts` reads coverage.py XML/JSON output. Move into `PythonProvider.parseCoverageReport()`.\n    25→- **OTLP packages**: `src/lib/otlp.ts` has `opentelemetry-sdk`, `opentelemetry-instrumentation` pip packages. Move into `PythonProvider.getOtlpPackages()`.\n    26→- **OTLP install**: `src/lib/otlp.ts` runs `pip install` / `pipx inject` for OTLP deps. Move into `PythonProvider.installOtlp()`.\n    27→- **Dockerfile template**: `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` has Python Dockerfile generation. Move into `PythonProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()`, `getDockerBuildStage()`, `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()`.\n    28→- **Docs scaffold**: `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` generates AGENTS.md with `pytest`, `pip install` commands. Move into `PythonProvider.getBuildCommands()`, `getTestCommands()`.\n    29→- **App type detection**: `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` checks for Flask/Django/FastAPI (server), CLI entry points, library patterns. Move into `PythonProvider.detectAppType()`.\n    30→- **Project name**: Read from `pyproject.toml` `[project] name` or `setup.py` name. Move into `PythonProvider.getProjectName()`.\n    31→\n    32→Markers: `['requirements.txt', 'pyproject.toml', 'setup.py']`. DisplayName: `'Python (requirements.txt)'` (or whichever marker matched). Semgrep languages: `['python']`.\n    33→\n    34→## Files to Change\n    35→\n    36→- `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` — Create. Implement `PythonProvider` class with all `StackProvider` methods\n    37→- `src/lib/stacks/registry.ts` — Register PythonProvider: `registry.set('python', new PythonProvider())`\n    38→- `src/lib/coverage.ts` — Remove Python-specific branches (coverage.py detection, pytest output parsing)\n    39→- `src/lib/otlp.ts` — Remove Python-specific OTLP package lists and install logic\n    40→- `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` — Remove Python Dockerfile template generation\n    41→- `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` — Remove Python-specific command generation\n    42→- `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` — Remove Python app type detection logic\n    43→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01LQDoB3frbVL8WR6YH4vVCs","session_id":"e39a20db-e648-4f8f-85ec-e4fa22cf8d05","uuid":"6ab1ce3e-dd5b-45b2-8a7b-79e403401390","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:20:54.522Z"}
