{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016g7gfyoNtGjDEf5Kd6mHG5","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 10-3: Implement PythonProvider\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->\n     3→\n     4→## Status: backlog\n     5→\n     6→## Story\n     7→\n     8→As a developer,\n     9→I want all Python-specific logic in one file,\n    10→So that Python behavior is encapsulated and testable in isolation.\n    11→\n    12→## Acceptance Criteria\n    13→\n    14→- [ ] AC1: Given `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` exists, when inspected, then it implements all `StackProvider` methods for Python: `detectAppType()` (server/cli/web/agent/generic from requirements.txt/pyproject.toml/setup.py), `getCoverageTool()` (returns `'coverage-py'`), `detectCoverageConfig()` (checks requirements.txt and pyproject.toml for `pytest-cov` or `coverage`), `getOtlpPackages()` (returns `['opentelemetry-distro', 'opentelemetry-exporter-otlp']`), `installOtlp()` (runs `pip install` with `pipx install` fallback), `getDockerfileTemplate()` (python:3.12-slim based), `getDockerBuildStage()` (multi-stage build snippet), `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` (COPY from build-python), `getBuildCommands()` (`['pip install -r requirements.txt']`), `getTestCommands()` (`['python -m pytest']`), `getSemgrepLanguages()` (`['python']`), `parseTestOutput()` (pytest format parsing), `parseCoverageReport()` (coverage.json parsing), `getProjectName()` (reads pyproject.toml `[project] name` or directory basename) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC2: Given a temporary directory with a `requirements.txt` containing `pytest-cov`, when `PythonProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'coverage-py' }` with a defined `configFile` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→- [ ] AC3: Given a temporary directory with a `pyproject.toml` containing `coverage` in its content, when `PythonProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` is called, then it returns `{ tool: 'coverage-py' }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC4: Given a temporary directory with a `requirements.txt` containing `anthropic`, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'agent'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC5: Given a temporary directory with a `requirements.txt` containing `flask` and a `templates/` directory, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'web'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC6: Given a temporary directory with a `requirements.txt` containing `fastapi` but no `templates/` or `static/` directory, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC7: Given a temporary directory with a `requirements.txt` containing `django` and a `manage.py` file, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` (web framework without templates/static dirs) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC8: Given a temporary directory with only a `requirements.txt` containing generic deps (no agent/web/server markers), and an `app.py` file, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'server'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC9: Given a temporary directory with only a `requirements.txt` containing generic deps and no entry-point files, when `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` is called, then it returns `'generic'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→- [ ] AC10: Given `PythonProvider.getOtlpPackages()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns exactly `['opentelemetry-distro', 'opentelemetry-exporter-otlp']` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→- [ ] AC11: Given `PythonProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM python:3.12-slim`, `pip install`, and `USER nobody` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→- [ ] AC12: Given `PythonProvider.getDockerBuildStage()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `FROM python:3.12-slim AS build-python` and `pip install --target=/build/dist .` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    26→- [ ] AC13: Given `PythonProvider.getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it contains `COPY --from=build-python` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    27→- [ ] AC14: Given pytest output text `12 passed, 3 failed`, when `PythonProvider.parseTestOutput()` is called, then it returns `{ passed: 12, failed: 3, skipped: 0, total: 15 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    28→- [ ] AC15: Given pytest output text `5 passed`, when `PythonProvider.parseTestOutput()` is called, then it returns `{ passed: 5, failed: 0, skipped: 0, total: 5 }` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    29→- [ ] AC16: Given a directory with `coverage.json` containing `{ \"totals\": { \"percent_covered\": 72.3 } }`, when `PythonProvider.parseCoverageReport()` is called, then it returns `72.3` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    30→- [ ] AC17: Given a directory without `coverage.json`, when `PythonProvider.parseCoverageReport()` is called, then it returns `0` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    31→- [ ] AC18: Given a directory with a `pyproject.toml` containing `[project]\\nname = \"my-python-app\"`, when `PythonProvider.getProjectName()` is called, then it returns `'my-python-app'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    32→- [ ] AC19: Given `PythonProvider.getSemgrepLanguages()` is called, when the result is inspected, then it returns `['python']` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    33→- [ ] AC20: Given `PythonProvider.getBuildCommands()` and `getTestCommands()` are called, when the results are inspected, then they return `['pip install -r requirements.txt']` and `['python -m pytest']` respectively <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    34→- [ ] AC21: Given unit tests exist in `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/python.test.ts`, when `npm test` runs, then all tests pass with 0 regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    35→\n    36→## Tasks/Subtasks\n    37→\n    38→- [ ] Task 1: Create `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` with `PythonProvider` class skeleton — Set `name: 'python'`, `markers: ['requirements.txt', 'pyproject.toml', 'setup.py']`, `displayName: 'Python'`. Import shared helpers from `./utils.js`.\n    39→- [ ] Task 2: Implement `PythonProvider.detectAppType()` — Extract Python app type detection from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` `detectAppType()` (the `stack === 'python'` branch). Read `requirements.txt`, `pyproject.toml`, `setup.py` content. Check deps for agent SDKs (`anthropic`, `openai`, `langchain`, `llama-index`, `traceloop-sdk`), web frameworks (`flask`, `django`, `fastapi`, `streamlit`) with `templates/`+`static/` dir checks, entry-point files (`app.py`, `main.py`, `manage.py`), fallback to `generic`.\n    40→- [ ] Task 3: Add `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` helpers to `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` — Extract from `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`. `getPythonDepsContent(dir)` reads and concatenates `requirements.txt`, `pyproject.toml`, `setup.py`. `hasPythonDep(content, dep)` matches package name with word-boundary regex to avoid substring false positives.\n    41→- [ ] Task 4: Implement `PythonProvider.getCoverageTool()` — Return `'coverage-py'` as the canonical Python coverage tool.\n    42→- [ ] Task 5: Implement `PythonProvider.detectCoverageConfig()` — Extract from `coverage.ts` `detectPythonCoverageTool()`. Check `requirements.txt` and `pyproject.toml` for `pytest-cov` or `coverage`. Return `CoverageToolInfo` with `tool: 'coverage-py'` and optional `configFile`.\n    43→- [ ] Task 6: Implement `PythonProvider.getOtlpPackages()` — Return the `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES` array from `otlp.ts`: `['opentelemetry-distro', 'opentelemetry-exporter-otlp']`.\n    44→- [ ] Task 7: Implement `PythonProvider.installOtlp()` — Extract from `otlp.ts` `installPythonOtlp()`. Primary: `pip install` both packages. Fallback: `pipx install` each package individually. Return `OtlpResult` with success/failure.\n    45→- [ ] Task 8: Implement `PythonProvider.getDockerfileTemplate()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `pythonTemplate()`. Return the python:3.12-slim Dockerfile string.\n    46→- [ ] Task 9: Implement `PythonProvider.getDockerBuildStage()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `pythonBuildStage()`. Return multi-stage build snippet with `FROM python:3.12-slim AS build-python`.\n    47→- [ ] Task 10: Implement `PythonProvider.getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` — Extract from `dockerfile-template.ts` `runtimeCopyDirectives()` (the python branch). Return `COPY --from=build-python /build/dist /opt/app/python/`.\n    48→- [ ] Task 11: Implement `PythonProvider.getBuildCommands()` — Return `['pip install -r requirements.txt']`.\n    49→- [ ] Task 12: Implement `PythonProvider.getTestCommands()` — Return `['python -m pytest']`.\n    50→- [ ] Task 13: Implement `PythonProvider.getSemgrepLanguages()` — Return `['python']`.\n    51→- [ ] Task 14: Implement `PythonProvider.parseTestOutput()` — Extract pytest parsing from `coverage.ts` `parseTestCounts()`. Pytest format: `N passed, M failed` or `N passed`. Return `TestCounts`.\n    52→- [ ] Task 15: Implement `PythonProvider.parseCoverageReport()` — Extract from `coverage.ts` `parsePythonCoverage()`. Read `coverage.json` in project dir, parse `totals.percent_covered`. Return `0` if file missing or malformed.\n    53→- [ ] Task 16: Implement `PythonProvider.getProjectName()` — Parse `pyproject.toml` for `[project]\\nname = \"...\"` using regex. Fallback to `setup.py` `name='...'` pattern. Return `null` if not found.\n    54→- [ ] Task 17: Register `PythonProvider` in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Add `import { PythonProvider } from './python.js'` and `registerProvider(new PythonProvider())` alongside existing NodejsProvider registration.\n    55→- [ ] Task 18: Create `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/python.test.ts` — Unit tests for every method. Use temp directories with fixture files. Cover: each app type variant (agent, web, server, cli, generic), coverage tool detection (pytest-cov in requirements.txt, coverage in pyproject.toml, neither), test output parsing (pytest passed+failed, passed only, no match), coverage report parsing (valid JSON, missing file, malformed), project name (pyproject.toml present, missing, no name field), OTLP packages, Dockerfile content, build/test commands, semgrep languages.\n    56→- [ ] Task 19: Verify the existing test suite still passes — run `npm test` and confirm 0 regressions.\n    57→\n    58→## Technical Notes\n    59→\n    60→**Decision 2 (Stack Provider Pattern).** Same structure as NodejsProvider (story 10-2). This is the second provider implementation.\n    61→\n    62→### What moves INTO PythonProvider\n    63→\n    64→| Method | Source File | Source Function/Branch |\n    65→|--------|------------|----------------------|\n    66→| `detectAppType()` | `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | `detectAppType()` → `stack === 'python'` branch |\n    67→| `getCoverageTool()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `detectCoverageTool()` → `stack === 'python'` branch |\n    68→| `detectCoverageConfig()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `detectPythonCoverageTool()` |\n    69→| `getOtlpPackages()` | `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES` constant |\n    70→| `installOtlp()` | `src/lib/otlp.ts` | `installPythonOtlp()` |\n    71→| `getDockerfileTemplate()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `pythonTemplate()` |\n    72→| `getDockerBuildStage()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `pythonBuildStage()` |\n    73→| `getRuntimeCopyDirectives()` | `src/modules/infra/dockerfile-template.ts` | `runtimeCopyDirectives()` python branch |\n    74→| `getBuildCommands()` | `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | `generateAgentsMdContent()` python branch |\n    75→| `getTestCommands()` | `src/modules/infra/docs-scaffold.ts` | `generateAgentsMdContent()` python branch |\n    76→| `getSemgrepLanguages()` | New | `['python']` |\n    77→| `parseTestOutput()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `parseTestCounts()` pytest branch |\n    78→| `parseCoverageReport()` | `src/lib/coverage.ts` | `parsePythonCoverage()` |\n    79→| `getProjectName()` | New | Parse `pyproject.toml` `[project] name` or `setup.py` `name=` |\n    80→\n    81→### What moves INTO shared utils\n    82→\n    83→| Helper | Source File | Notes |\n    84→|--------|------------|-------|\n    85→| `getPythonDepsContent()` | `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | Reads requirements.txt + pyproject.toml + setup.py |\n    86→| `hasPythonDep()` | `src/lib/stack-detect.ts` | Word-boundary regex match for Python package names |\n    87→\n    88→### Important: Do NOT remove consumer branches yet\n    89→\n    90→This story implements the provider methods only. Consumer files (`coverage.ts`, `otlp.ts`, `docs-scaffold.ts`, `dockerfile-template.ts`, `stack-detect.ts`) keep their existing if/else branches for now. Story 10-5 migrates consumers to use `provider.method()` and removes the branches. This avoids a big-bang migration.\n    91→\n    92→### Python app type detection constants\n    93→\n    94→From `src/lib/stack-detect.ts`:\n    95→- `AGENT_DEPS_PYTHON = ['anthropic', 'openai', 'langchain', 'llama-index', 'traceloop-sdk']`\n    96→- `PYTHON_WEB_FRAMEWORKS = ['flask', 'django', 'fastapi', 'streamlit']`\n    97→- Server entry points: `app.py`, `main.py`, `manage.py`\n    98→- Web detection requires framework dep AND (`templates/` or `static/` directory)\n    99→\n   100→### CoverageToolInfo mapping\n   101→\n   102→The `CoverageToolInfo` in `stacks/types.ts` has `{ tool: CoverageToolName; configFile?: string }`. The current `coverage.ts` `CoverageToolInfo` has `{ tool: string; runCommand: string; reportFormat: string }`. The provider's `detectCoverageConfig()` returns the stacks/types version. The `runCommand` and `reportFormat` can be derived from the tool name by the consumer or added to the provider as separate methods if needed during story 10-5.\n   103→\n   104→### OTLP install strategy\n   105→\n   106→`installOtlp()` uses a two-chain fallback: primary `pip install opentelemetry-distro opentelemetry-exporter-otlp`, fallback `pipx install` for each package individually (pipx only accepts one package at a time). Returns `OtlpResult` matching the interface in `stacks/types.ts`.\n   107→\n   108→## Dev Notes\n   109→\n   110→- The `NodejsProvider` in `src/lib/stacks/nodejs.ts` is the reference implementation — follow its structure exactly.\n   111→- Registration in `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` already registers NodejsProvider; add PythonProvider registration alongside it.\n   112→- `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` already has `readJsonSafe()`, `readTextSafe()`, `getNodeDeps()` — add `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` there.\n   113→- No `patchStartScript()` method for Python — the OTLP Python wrapper (`opentelemetry-instrument`) is configured via env vars, not source patching.\n   114→\n   115→## Files to Change\n   116→\n   117→- `src/lib/stacks/python.ts` — Create. Implement `PythonProvider` class with all `StackProvider` methods\n   118→- `src/lib/stacks/utils.ts` — Add `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` helpers (extracted from `stack-detect.ts`)\n   119→- `src/lib/stacks/index.ts` — Register PythonProvider: `registerProvider(new PythonProvider())`\n   120→- `src/lib/__tests__/stacks/python.test.ts` — Create. Comprehensive unit tests for all PythonProvider methods\n   121→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01BmxG7qx6yQHWseU1bwDgY4","session_id":"e39a20db-e648-4f8f-85ec-e4fa22cf8d05","uuid":"3142dbd2-c07b-459f-bd0d-0bbaed311e8a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:23:50.395Z"}
