{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01XXdV3K3gysdv7HwBLXK2M3","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Everything looks correct. Here's the summary:\n\n---\n\n## Review Complete\n\n**Story:** 10-3-python-provider (PythonProvider implementation)\n**Status:** Updated to `verifying`\n**Tests:** 75 pass (up from 62), full suite 3342 pass (0 regressions)\n**Coverage:** 97.11% overall, all 129 files above 80% per-file floor\n\n### Issues Found and Fixed (4 total)\n\n**HIGH (1):**\n- `detectCoverageConfig` in `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/python.ts` used `String.includes('coverage')` for requirements.txt matching, which false-positives on packages like `coverage-conditional-plugin`. Switched to `hasPythonDep()` for word-boundary matching in requirements.txt. For pyproject.toml, added `[tool.coverage` section detection alongside `hasPythonDep()`.\n\n**MEDIUM (3):**\n- `installOtlp` pipx fallback reported `packagesInstalled: []` even when the first package succeeded but the second failed. Fixed to track actually installed packages incrementally.\n- `getProjectName` regex `(?:.*\\n)*?` could cross TOML section boundaries, matching a `name` field under `[tool.poetry]` when `[project]` had no name. Rewrote to extract the `[project]` section first, then search within it.\n- No direct unit tests for `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` utils. Added 13 new tests covering these functions and edge cases.\n\n### Files Modified\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/stacks/python.ts` — Fixed detectCoverageConfig, installOtlp, getProjectName\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/__tests__/stacks/python.test.ts` — Added 13 tests (utils, regression, section-crossing)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-3-python-provider.md` — Status to verifying, change log updated\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and fixed:**\n- HIGH: `detectCoverageConfig` substring false positives on requirements.txt (e.g. `coverage-conditional-plugin` would match as having coverage tool)\n- MEDIUM: `installOtlp` pipx fallback loses track of partially installed packages\n- MEDIUM: `getProjectName` TOML section-crossing regex bug\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- `detectCoverageConfig` still uses `readFileSync` in `parseCoverageReport` while other methods use `readTextSafe` — minor inconsistency, not worth the churn\n- `hasPythonDep` matches package names inside comments (e.g. `# coverage` in requirements.txt) — pre-existing behavior inherited from original `stack-detect.ts`, would require comment-stripping to fix properly; very low real-world impact\n- Task comment markers (`// -- Task N:`) are implementation scaffolding that could be removed for cleaner production code\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- `installOtlp` success path (pip/pipx actually working) is not tested because it requires real `pip`/`pipx` binaries — needs integration test harness or mock\n- No tests for `detectCoverageConfig` when file read permissions are denied (OS-level edge case)\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. The provider pattern is clean and consistent with NodejsProvider.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed in this session."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a47d4f51d9ba2c038 (use SendMessage with to: 'a47d4f51d9ba2c038' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 61076\ntool_uses: 46\nduration_ms: 274012</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e39a20db-e648-4f8f-85ec-e4fa22cf8d05","uuid":"5377c0a7-dceb-4328-abd7-7d5fbf4a2903","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:33:27.322Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/10-3-python-provider.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files 