{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012PCpXHjYsAP2qWtyZdCPPy","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 3)\n     2→\n     3→### 10-3-python-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T08:23Z)\n     4→\n     5→- **Workaround:** Epic mentions CLI/library detection for Python app types, but codebase only has agent/web/server/generic. ACs reflect actual code, not aspirational epic text.\n     6→- **Risk:** `getProjectName()` uses TOML regex (fragile for edge cases). Proper TOML parser would be better but adds dependency.\n     7→- **Risk:** `hasPythonDep()` regex fragile for packages with hyphens/underscores (Python normalizes these).\n     8→- **Observation:** `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES` in code are `opentelemetry-distro`/`opentelemetry-exporter-otlp`, not what the original story skeleton stated.\n     9→- **Observation:** Python has no `patchStartScript()` — uses `opentelemetry-instrument` wrapper via env vars instead.\n    10→\n    11→### 10-3-python-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:28Z)\n    12→\n    13→No issues reported. 62 new tests pass, 3329 total, 0 regressions.\n    14→\n    15→### 10-3-python-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T08:33Z)\n    16→\n    17→- **HIGH (fixed):** `detectCoverageConfig` substring false positives — `String.includes('coverage')` matched `coverage-conditional-plugin`. Switched to `hasPythonDep()`.\n    18→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `installOtlp` pipx fallback lost track of partially installed packages.\n    19→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getProjectName` TOML regex crossed section boundaries.\n    20→- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing direct tests for `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` utils — added 13 tests.\n    21→- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasPythonDep` matches package names inside comments — pre-existing behavior, low real-world impact.\n    22→- **LOW (not fixed):** Task comment markers in code could be cleaned up.\n    23→- **Coverage gap:** `installOtlp` success path untested (needs real pip/pipx binaries).\n    24→\n    25→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e39a20db-e648-4f8f-85ec-e4fa22cf8d05","uuid":"5c2aec82-388d-4770-83e5-b7e8beeb633a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T08:34:38.995Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","content":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24 (session 3)\n\n### 10-3-python-provider — create-story (2026-03-24T08:23Z)\n\n- **Workaround:** Epic mentions CLI/library detection for Python app types, but codebase only has agent/web/server/generic. ACs reflect actual code, not aspirational epic text.\n- **Risk:** `getProjectName()` uses TOML regex (fragile for edge cases). Proper TOML parser would be better but adds dependency.\n- **Risk:** `hasPythonDep()` regex fragile for packages with hyphens/underscores (Python normalizes these).\n- **Observation:** `PYTHON_OTLP_PACKAGES` in code are `opentelemetry-distro`/`opentelemetry-exporter-otlp`, not what the original story skeleton stated.\n- **Observation:** Python has no `patchStartScript()` — uses `opentelemetry-instrument` wrapper via env vars instead.\n\n### 10-3-python-provider — dev-story (2026-03-24T08:28Z)\n\nNo issues reported. 62 new tests pass, 3329 total, 0 regressions.\n\n### 10-3-python-provider — code-review (2026-03-24T08:33Z)\n\n- **HIGH (fixed):** `detectCoverageConfig` substring false positives — `String.includes('coverage')` matched `coverage-conditional-plugin`. Switched to `hasPythonDep()`.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `installOtlp` pipx fallback lost track of partially installed packages.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** `getProjectName` TOML regex crossed section boundaries.\n- **MEDIUM (fixed):** Missing direct tests for `getPythonDepsContent()` and `hasPythonDep()` utils — added 13 tests.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** `hasPythonDep` matches package names inside comments — pre-existing behavior, low real-world impact.\n- **LOW (not fixed):** Task comment markers in code could be cleaned up.\n- **Coverage gap:** `installOtlp` success path untested (needs real pip/pipx binaries).\n\n","numLines":25,"startLine":1,"totalLines":25}}}
